  "texts": [
    "The ASOPS THz-TDS can achieve precise spectroscopy by simultaneously using all the modes that compose the optical comb for frequency referencing [121], [122].",
    "However, due to the limited optical power of each comb mode in the order of sub-nanowatts, increasing the number of averages is essential for achieving a high dynamic range.",
    "Yet, the dynamic range of this scheme is limited, reaching a level of 40 dB for 1000 averages [105]- [107], compared to the 90 dB dynamic range of conventional mechanically scanned systems [104].",
    "Peak dynamic range refers to the largest dynamic range observed in the measured spectrum, typically occurring at 0.5 THz in THz-TDS and 0.1 THz in CW THz spectroscopy.",
    "As the range tends to increase gradually in the 0.1-0.5 THz range in THz-TDS, there might be constraints in evaluating components operating in the sub-0.5 THz range."
  ],
